# UI Consistency First (Mandatory)

Before any UI edit:

1. Inspect nearby existing sections and reuse their typography, spacing, and button scale.
2. Treat screenshot dimensions as reference for structure/style only, not literal pixel scaling.
3. Do not introduce larger heading, body, button, or card sizes than adjacent sections unless explicitly requested.
4. Prefer existing tokens/classes over new one-off size values.

When implementing visual changes:

- Keep H2, card titles, body text, and button sizes aligned with current page baseline.
- If a change risks upsizing elements, choose the smaller consistent option.
- Match layout and styling details from screenshots while preserving established scale.

Regression guard:

- After edits, verify affected section still matches the same size hierarchy as neighboring sections.
- If user asks to reduce size, apply immediately and keep that scale for subsequent edits.
